---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Web Design for Restaurants | FisherDigital"
  description="Websites for restaurants, cafes, and takeaways across the UK. Show your menu, take bookings online, and stop paying 30% commission to delivery apps for orders you could handle yourself."
  schemaType="niche"
  niche="Restaurants"
  nicheDescription="Professional websites, online menus, and booking systems built specifically for restaurants, cafes, and takeaways in the UK."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-light py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span class="label block mb-4">Web design for restaurants</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-6">
          Fill tables, not someone<br />
          <span class="text-accent">else's pockets.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)] max-w-xl mb-10 leading-relaxed">
          Delivery apps take 30% of every order. Booking platforms charge per cover. Meanwhile, your own website is a single page with last year's menu as a PDF. We build restaurant websites that bring customers direct, where you keep the full margin.
        </p>
        <a href="/#contact" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-accent text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-600 hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all shadow-lg shadow-accent/20 hover:shadow-accent/40">
          Book a free call
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pain Points -->
  <section class="bg-white py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="label block mb-4">The problem</span>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight">
          You're paying for problems you don't need.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Pain 1 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">Delivery apps eating your margins</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            Deliveroo, Just Eat, and Uber Eats take up to 30% per order. On a busy Friday, that's hundreds of pounds going to middlemen. Direct orders through your own site cost you nothing extra.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pain 2 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h7"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">Menu buried in a PDF nobody opens</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            A PDF menu doesn't work on mobile. It's slow to load, impossible to read without zooming, and invisible to Google. When someone searches "Italian restaurant [your area]," your menu should be on the page, not in a download.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Pain 3 -->
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-border)] p-8 bg-[var(--color-surface-light)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-accent" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M3 5a2 2 0 012-2h3.28a1 1 0 01.948.684l1.498 4.493a1 1 0 01-.502 1.21l-2.257 1.13a11.042 11.042 0 005.516 5.516l1.13-2.257a1 1 0 011.21-.502l4.493 1.498a1 1 0 01.684.949V19a2 2 0 01-2 2h-1C9.716 21 3 14.284 3 6V5z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-600 mb-3">Saturday night phone ringing off the hook</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            Your busiest night is also when the most bookings come in by phone. Staff are plating food, not answering calls. Every missed call is an empty table. Online booking solves this without adding headcount.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Build -->
  <section class="section-light py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <span class="label block mb-4">What you get</span>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-12">
          Your restaurant, looking its best online.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Beautiful, browsable menu on every screen</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">Your full menu displayed as a proper web page. Easy to read on phones, organised by category, with descriptions and prices. Updated any time with a quick message to us.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Table booking built into the site</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">Customers pick a date, time, and party size. You get a notification. No third-party booking platform taking a cut. Works on the Essential plan upward.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">Food photography that makes people hungry</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">We optimise your photos for fast loading without killing the quality. Rich, full-bleed images of your food, your dining room, and your team. The site should make someone want to eat there tonight.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent mt-1 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            <div>
              <p class="font-600 text-[var(--color-light-text)] mb-1">AI chatbot that handles reservations and FAQs</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-light-text-secondary)]">On the Professional plan, a chatbot answers "are you open Mondays?", "do you cater for allergies?", and "can I book for 8 this Friday?" without staff lifting a finger.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-white py-(--spacing-section)">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-600 tracking-tight mb-6">
        See a restaurant site we built.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-xl mx-auto mb-10">
        The Olive Press is a demo site showing how a restaurant can look online. Full menu, booking section, reviews, Google Maps. Have a look, then let's talk about yours.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-5">
        <a href="/demos/the-olive-press/" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-accent text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-600 hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all shadow-lg shadow-accent/20 hover:shadow-accent/40">
          See a live demo
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/#contact" data-hover
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-500 border border-[var(--color-border-light)] hover:border-accent hover:text-accent transition-all">
          Book a free call
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
